<P>Newes come <HI>latle fro~ Pera, of two mo&s;t mighti</HI> Armies as wel of Foteme~ as of Hor&s;+me~, tra~&s;lated out of Italien, to Fre~|che and &s;o into Engle&s;he. And fir&s;t of the great Duke of Mo&s;couia &amp; of the Soffy, And y^e othere of an Hebrewe people neuer &s;poken of before, fou~de not lo~g ago comming from y^e Moun|taines called Ca&s;pii, with a newe in|uencio~ of Weapons, with y^e nomber of y^e Squadrons, and with the names of two Earles &amp; Capitayns. And the cau&s;e whi y^e great Turk hath forbyd|de~ wyne, with mani other newes ne|uer hard of.</P>
<P><FIGURE>
<FIGDESC>depiction of two groups of knights in armour on horseback charging each other, with weapons and bodies on the ground</FIGDESC>
</FIGURE></P>
</DIV1>
